SIMPLE: transcendent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Transcendent
<hw>Tran*scend"ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>transcendens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>transcendere</ets> to transcend: cf. F. <ets>transcendant</ets>, G.
<ets>transcendent</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Very excellent;
superior or supreme in excellence; surpassing others; <as>as,
<ex>transcendent</ex> worth; <ex>transcendent</ex> valor</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Clothed with <qex>transcendent</qex> brightness.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Kantian Philos.)</fld> <def>Transcending, or
reaching beyond, the limits of human knowledge; -- applied to
affirmations and speculations concerning what lies beyond the reach of
the human intellect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transcendent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Transcendent
<hw>Tran*scend"ent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which surpasses or is
supereminent; that which is very excellent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transcendental</ent>⟦br⟧
